<p><strong><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/author/renee-h-shea">Renee H. Shea</a></strong>, formerly professor of English at Bowie State University in Maryland, interviews contemporary authors for <em>World Literature Today</em>. She frequently contributes to <em>Poets &amp; Writers</em>, most recently “Hope and Terror,” a profile of Julia Phillips (July/August 2024), and “Alone Together,” a profile of Edwidge Danticat (September/October 2024). She is currently doing a series for the <a href="https://americanbookreview.org/"><em>American Book Review</em></a> on “The Laureates.” The initial interview with J.&nbsp;Drew Lanham, poet laureate of Edgefield County, South Carolina, appeared in the fall 2023 issue. She also coauthors English language arts textbooks for Bedford, Freeman &amp; Worth.</p>
